      "content": "I'll modify the query to use parameterized queries, which is the recommended way to prevent SQL injection attacks. This will also make it easier to debug and maintain the code.\n\n```python\nimport sqlite3\n\ndef login_user(username, password):\n    conn = sqlite3.connect('users.db')\n    cursor = conn.cursor()\n    \n    query = \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = ? AND password = ?\"\n    cursor.execute(query, (username, password))\n    user = cursor.fetchone()\n    \n    if user:\n        return True\n    else:\n        return False\n```\n\nBy using parameterized queries, we're telling the database to treat the username and password as variables, rather than literal strings. This prevents the scanner from flagging the code as vulnerable to SQL injection attacks.",
